ws are often restricted to high-energy diets with controlled feeding periods and limited movement.\n- Modern breeding and optimal feed combinations aim to maximize milk output. Generally, dairy cows are milked only during their most productive years, utilizing practices aimed at maintaining efficiency and health, such as controlled breeding and dietary management.\n\nThis summary excludes any figures or tables that might be referenced but not visible in the provided text. The emphasis is on key facts about milk biology, casein proteins, and the influence of dairy industry practices."
